Regression Analysis on House, BIST and Employment Statistics¶

Introduction¶

The main objective of this study is to analyze some of the most important economical statistics of Turkey with Linear Regression models to gain information about their relations to other economical or social metrics. The source code of the analysis can be found here.

The study consist of three analysis, each having different target variable. Potential economical and social features are analyzed and refined subsets of these features are used in the study to lessen the complexity.

The data, available in the Data folder, for this study is mostly gathered through Central Bank of the Republic of Turkey's EVDS API and Google Trends. The only feature which is not gathered from these sources is a binary variable to represent whether there are considerable amount of Covid-19 cases in Turkey or not. The source of this feature is Ministry of Health's daily reports.

In [2]:
def get_best_lag(x, y, lags, x_label, y_label, title):
    '''Determine best lag (highest correlation) in a given range for a feature'''
    cross_corr_arr = [0]*lags
    for lag in range(lags):
        lag_corr = np.corrcoef(x.shift(lag).iloc[lag:], y.iloc[lag:])[0, 1]
        cross_corr_arr[lag] = lag_corr

    # Cross Correlation Plot
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 9))
    plt.plot(cross_corr_arr)
    plt.xlabel(x_label)
    plt.ylabel(y_label)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.show()

    # Return highest correlated lag
    return np.argmax(np.abs(cross_corr_arr))

House Sales¶

Housing is an important part of the Turkey economy in the recent years. Even though there are a lot of economical instability, it is expected for house sales to have less variance when compared to other financial statistics such as exchange rates or inflation. This is because even though house sales are related with economy (prices, interest rates etc.), they have more independent social factors that have impacts on the monthly average house sales.

Interested questions in this analysis:

  • Does online house search have impact on house sales?
  • Does online wedding hall search, which have the information of new marriages, have impact on house sales?
  • Does online real estate search, which can have information about house investments, have impact on house sales?
  • Does online foreign house search, which can include information about migrations' effect, have impact on house sales?
  • Did Covid-19 have an effect on housing?
  • Is there a trend or seasonality in the house sales?

The model performance seems fine (for a linear model that is predicting an economical variable in the current environment of economy and the data quality). All variables seems to be significant, therefore Google search about houses seems to be significant to explain their sales. The intercept here includes the effect of other months that are dropped while other seasonal variables' coefficient indicates their difference from the other months.

Residual analysis is needed to be more confident about the current model and whether the assumptions hold about Linear Regression.

Since p value > .05, we fail to reject the null hypothesis that residuals are not autocorrelated up to and including lag 12. Therefore, assumption of independent errors holds for this model, even though it is not with very high confidence level. Therefore all assumptions of the linear regression holds for this model with not very high confidence levels.

BIST Volume¶

BIST is Turkey's main stock exchange platform which makes it very important for the Turkish economy. The volume of the trades in BIST can indicate the interest to the stock market and investments. It is expected for BIST volume to be very volitile in current conditions and therefore hard to model with a linear model (or maybe with any model depending on data quality). BIST volume will be analyzed in terms of USD.

Interested questions in this analysis:

  • Does interest rates have an effect on BIST volume?
  • Does online stock market search, impact BIST volume?
  • Does online gold search, which indicates the interest in investments, have an impact on BIST volume?
  • Does USD exchange rate have impact on BIST volume even though volume is in terms of dollars?
  • Is there a trend or seasonality in the BIST volume?

Unemployment¶

Unemployment is an highly important economical and social parameter. With the current conditions, it is expected to be hard to predict. This is because even though it is not in monetary terms, it is influenced by economical conditions a lot.

Interested questions in this analysis:

  • Does online Linkedin search affect the unemployment?
  • Does online job search have an impact on the unemployment?
  • Does USD exchange rate have an effect on the unemployment?
  • Did Covid-19 have an effect on the unemployment?
  • Is there a trend or seasonality in the the unemployment?

Conclusion¶

The aim of this study was to analyze economical parameters in Turkey to explain their relations to other economical or social variables. Three analysis were done:

1- House Sales The main questions that were analyzed:

  • Does online house search have impact on house sales? => Yes, significantly.
  • Does online wedding hall search have impact on house sales? => Yes, significantly.
  • Does online real estate search have impact on house sales? => Yes, however since other variables explains it, this feature is not significant for the model.
  • Does online foreign house search have impact on house sales? => Yes, significantly.
  • Did Covid-19 have an effect on housing? => Yes, significantly.
  • Is there a trend or seasonality in the house sales? => Yes, significantly.

2- BIST Volume The main questions that were analyzed:

  • Does interest rates have an effect on BIST volume? => Yes, significantly.
  • Does online stock market search, impact BIST volume? => Yes, significantly.
  • Does online gold search have an impact on BIST volume? => Yes, significantly.
  • Does USD exchange rate have impact on BIST volume? => Yes, significantly.
  • Is there a trend or seasonality in the BIST volume? => Yes, significantly.

3- Unemployment The main questions that were analyzed:

  • Does online Linkedin search affect the unemployment? => Yes, however, since its effect is explained by other variables, it is not significant for the model.
  • Does online job search have an impact on the unemployment? => Yes, significantly.
  • Does USD exchange rate have an effect on the unemployment? => Yes, significantly.
  • Did Covid-19 have an effect on the unemployment? => Yes, significantly.
  • Is there a trend or seasonality in the the unemployment? => Yes, significantly.

Also to further improve the model, the binary feauture which indicates whether it is post election or not is added. This feature significantly improved the model which indicates that a pattern change happaned for the unemployment.
